The Todo Academy, the setting for the broadcast series Tenjho Tenge (2004), was created to revive Tokugawa era martial arts: it's a high school of brawling thugs, ruled by a student "executive council."     After the bloody fight between Shin and Bunshichi, the Katana gang breaks up and Mitsuomi's life is forever changed.
 Back to the present, the Juken club's resolve has grown ever stronger with Maya's story - a much needed source of strength when the entire school targets the club after their incident with the Executive Council. But another bomb is dropped when Maya receives a severe sentence by the school.
